===Etymology===
Via {{etyl|enm}} < {{etyl|ang}} ''[[dæg|dæġ]]'' < {{proto|Germanic|dagaz}} < {{proto|Indo-European|dhegh-|to burn}}. Not related to Latin ''[[dies]]'' (< {{proto|Indo-European|dyeu-|to shine}}), but rather to Sanskrit ''dāhas'' ‘heat’ < {{proto|Indo-European|dhegh-|to burn}}. Cognates include Swedish and Dutch ''[[dag]]'' and German ''[[Tag]]'' ‘day’.

